#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an6.62"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.62:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:0.2"
msgid "6. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "6. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.62:0.3"
msgid "62. Purisindriyañāṇasutta "
msgstr "62. Knowledge of the Faculties of Persons "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an6.62:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "an6.62:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ yena daṇḍakappakaṃ nāma kosalānaṃ nigamo tadavasari. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a town of the Kosalans named Daṇḍakappaka. "

msgctxt "an6.62:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā maggā okkamma aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle paññatte āsane nisīdi. "
msgstr "The Buddha left the road and sat at the root of a tree on the seat spread out. "

msgctxt "an6.62:1.4"
msgid "Te ca bhikkhū daṇḍakappakaṃ pavisiṃsu āvasathaṃ pariyesituṃ. "
msgstr "The mendicants entered Daṇḍakappaka to look for a guest house. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an6.62:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ yena aciravatī nadī tenupasaṅkami gattāni parisiñcituṃ. "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda together with several mendicants went to the Aciravati River to bathe. "

msgctxt "an6.62:2.2"
msgid "Aciravatiyā nadiyā gattāni parisiñcitvā paccuttaritvā ekacīvaro aṭṭhāsi gattāni pubbāpayamāno. "
msgstr "When he had bathed and emerged from the water he stood in one robe drying himself. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a certain mendicant went up to Venerable Ānanda, and said to him, "

msgctxt "an6.62:2.4"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho, āvuso ānanda, sabbaṃ cetaso samannāharitvā nu kho devadatto bhagavatā byākato: "
msgstr "“Reverend Ānanda, when the Buddha declared that Devadatta was "

msgctxt "an6.62:2.5"
msgid "‘āpāyiko devadatto nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho’ti, udāhu kenacideva pariyāyenāti? "
msgstr "going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable, did he do so after wholeheartedly deliberating, or was this just a way of speaking?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:2.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā byākatan”ti. "
msgstr "“You’re right, reverend, that’s how the Buddha declared it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.403, sc3
msgctxt "an6.62:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. "

msgctxt "an6.62:3.2"
msgid "“idhāhaṃ, bhante, sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ yena aciravatī nadī tenupasaṅkamiṃ gattāni parisiñcituṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.62:3.3"
msgid "Aciravatiyā nadiyā gattāni parisiñcitvā paccuttaritvā ekacīvaro aṭṭhāsiṃ gattāni pubbāpayamāno. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.62:3.4"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, aññataro bhikkhu yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.62:3.5"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho, āvuso ānanda, sabbaṃ cetaso samannāharitvā nu kho devadatto bhagavatā byākato—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.62:3.6"
msgid "āpāyiko devadatto nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekicchoti, udāhu kenacideva pariyāyenā’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.62:3.7"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhante, taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.62:3.8"
msgid "‘evaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā byākatan’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: vā → so ca (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.62:4.1"
msgid "“So vā kho, ānanda, bhikkhu navo bhavissati acirapabbajito, thero vā pana bālo abyatto. "
msgstr "“Ānanda, that mendicant must be junior, recently gone forth, or else a foolish, incompetent senior mendicant. "

msgctxt "an6.62:4.2"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma yaṃ mayā ekaṃsena byākataṃ tattha dvejjhaṃ āpajjissati. "
msgstr "How on earth can he take something that I have declared definitively to be ambiguous? "

msgctxt "an6.62:4.3"
msgid "Nāhaṃ, ānanda, aññaṃ ekapuggalampi samanupassāmi, yo evaṃ mayā sabbaṃ cetaso samannāharitvā byākato, yathayidaṃ devadatto. "
msgstr "I do not see a single other person concerning whom I have made a declaration about after giving such wholehearted deliberation as Devadatta. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:4.4"
msgid "Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, ānanda, devadattassa vālaggakoṭinittudanamattampi sukkadhammaṃ addasaṃ; "
msgstr "As long as I saw even a fraction of a hair’s tip of goodness in Devadatta "

msgctxt "an6.62:4.5"
msgid "neva tāvāhaṃ devadattaṃ byākāsiṃ: "
msgstr "I did not declare that he was "

msgctxt "an6.62:4.6"
msgid "‘āpāyiko devadatto nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho’ti. "
msgstr "going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable. "

msgctxt "an6.62:4.7"
msgid "Yato ca kho ahaṃ, ānanda, devadattassa vālaggakoṭinittudanamattampi sukkadhammaṃ na addasaṃ; "
msgstr "But when I saw that there was not even a fraction of a hair’s tip of goodness in Devadatta "

msgctxt "an6.62:4.8"
msgid "athāhaṃ devadattaṃ byākāsiṃ: "
msgstr "I declared that he was "

msgctxt "an6.62:4.9"
msgid "‘āpāyiko devadatto nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho’ti. "
msgstr "going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.404, sc5
msgctxt "an6.62:5.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, gūthakūpo sādhikaporiso pūro gūthassa samatittiko. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a sewer deeper than a man’s height, full to the brim with feces, "

msgctxt "an6.62:5.2"
msgid "Tatra puriso sasīsako nimuggo assa. "
msgstr "and someone was sunk into it over their head. "

msgctxt "an6.62:5.3"
msgid "Tassa kocideva puriso uppajjeyya atthakāmo hitakāmo yogakkhemakāmo tamhā gūthakūpā uddharitukāmo. "
msgstr "Then along comes a person who wants to help make them safe, who wants to lift them out of that sewer. "

msgctxt "an6.62:5.4"
msgid "So taṃ gūthakūpaṃ samantānuparigacchanto neva passeyya tassa purisassa vālaggakoṭinittudanamattampi gūthena amakkhitaṃ, yattha taṃ gahetvā uddhareyya. "
msgstr "But circling all around the sewer they couldn’t see even a fraction of a hair’s tip on that person that was not smeared with feces. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:5.5"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, ānanda, yato devadattassa vālaggakoṭinittudanamattampi sukkadhammaṃ na addasaṃ; "
msgstr "In the same way, when I saw that there was not even a fraction of a hair’s tip of goodness in Devadatta "

msgctxt "an6.62:5.6"
msgid "athāhaṃ devadattaṃ byākāsiṃ: "
msgstr "I declared that he was "

msgctxt "an6.62:5.7"
msgid "‘āpāyiko devadatto nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho’ti. "
msgstr "going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable. "

# NOTE: This specific phrasing is shared with MN 136 and AN 6.62. In both cases, the context follows a case where a junior monk has made a silly statement. I think the phrasing is meant to express a certain frustration, if I may dare to use such a term of the Buddha! The parsing of vibhajantassa is problematic, see BB’s note on AN 6.62.
#. VAR: vibhajissāmī”ti → vibhajantassāti (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.62:5.8"
msgid "Sace tumhe, ānanda, suṇeyyātha tathāgatassa purisindriyañāṇāni vibhajissāmī”ti? "
msgstr "Ānanda, if only you would all listen to the Realized One’s analysis of the knowledges of the faculties of individuals.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an6.62:6.1"
msgid "“Etassa, bhagavā, kālo; etassa, sugata, kālo "
msgstr "“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One! "

msgctxt "an6.62:6.2"
msgid "yaṃ bhagavā purisindriyañāṇāni vibhajeyya. Bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti. "
msgstr "Let the Buddha analyze the faculties of persons. The mendicants will listen and remember it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:6.3"
msgid "“Tenahānanda, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:6.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied. "

msgctxt "an6.62:6.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.405, sc7
msgctxt "an6.62:7.1"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, ānanda, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
msgstr "“Ānanda, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand: "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.2"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Both skillful and unskillful qualities are found in this person.’ "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
msgstr "After some time I comprehend their mind and understand: "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.4"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa kusalā dhammā antarahitā, akusalā dhammā sammukhībhūtā. "
msgstr "‘The skillful qualities of this person have vanished, but the unskillful qualities are still present. "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.5"
msgid "Atthi ca khvassa kusalamūlaṃ asamucchinnaṃ, tamhā tassa kusalā kusalaṃ pātubhavissati. "
msgstr "Nevertheless, their skillful root is unbroken, and from that the skillful will appear. "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.6"
msgid "Evamayaṃ puggalo āyatiṃ aparihānadhammo bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "So this person is not liable to decline in the future.’ "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, bījāni akhaṇḍāni apūtīni avātātapahatāni sāradāni sukhasayitāni sukhette suparikammakatāya bhūmiyā nikkhittāni. "
msgstr "Suppose some seeds were intact, unspoiled, not weather-damaged, fertile, and well-kept. They’re sown in a well-prepared, productive field. "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.8"
msgid "Jāneyyāsi tvaṃ, ānanda, imāni bījāni vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissantī”ti? "
msgstr "Wouldn’t you know that those seeds would grow, increase, and mature?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:7.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:7.10"
msgid "“Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, ānanda, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
msgstr "“In the same way, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand … "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.11"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.12"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.13"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa kusalā dhammā antarahitā, akusalā dhammā sammukhībhūtā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.14"
msgid "Atthi ca khvassa kusalamūlaṃ asamucchinnaṃ, tamhā tassa kusalā kusalaṃ pātubhavissati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.15"
msgid "Evamayaṃ puggalo āyatiṃ aparihānadhammo bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "This person is not liable to decline in the future … "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.16"
msgid "Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa purisapuggalo cetasā ceto paricca vidito hoti. "
msgstr "This is how another individual is known to the Realized One by comprehending their mind. "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.17"
msgid "Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa purisindriyañāṇaṃ cetasā ceto paricca viditaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "And this is how the Realized One knows a person’s faculties by comprehending their mind. "

msgctxt "an6.62:7.18"
msgid "Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa āyatiṃ dhammasamuppādo cetasā ceto paricca vidito hoti. (1) "
msgstr "And this is how the Realized One knows the future origination of a person’s qualities by comprehending their mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.406, sc8
msgctxt "an6.62:8.1"
msgid "Idha panāhaṃ, ānanda, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
msgstr "When I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand: "

msgctxt "an6.62:8.2"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Both skillful and unskillful qualities are found in this person.’ "

msgctxt "an6.62:8.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
msgstr "After some time I comprehend their mind and understand: "

msgctxt "an6.62:8.4"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa akusalā dhammā antarahitā, kusalā dhammā sammukhībhūtā. "
msgstr "‘The unskillful qualities of this person have vanished, but the skillful qualities are still present. "

msgctxt "an6.62:8.5"
msgid "Atthi ca khvassa akusalamūlaṃ asamucchinnaṃ, tamhā tassa akusalā akusalaṃ pātubhavissati. "
msgstr "Nevertheless, their unskillful root is unbroken, and from that the unskillful will appear. "

msgctxt "an6.62:8.6"
msgid "Evamayaṃ puggalo āyatiṃ parihānadhammo bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "So this person is still liable to decline in the future.’ "

msgctxt "an6.62:8.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, bījāni akhaṇḍāni apūtīni avātātapahatāni sāradāni sukhasayitāni puthusilāya nikkhittāni. "
msgstr "Suppose some seeds were intact, unspoiled, not weather-damaged, fertile, and well-kept. And they were sown on a broad rock. "

msgctxt "an6.62:8.8"
msgid "Jāneyyāsi tvaṃ, ānanda, nayimāni bījāni vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissantī”ti? "
msgstr "Wouldn’t you know that those seeds would not grow, increase, and mature?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:8.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:8.10"
msgid "“Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, ānanda, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
msgstr "“In the same way, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand … "

msgctxt "an6.62:8.11"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.62:8.12"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
