msgid "Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa purisindriyañāṇaṃ cetasā ceto paricca viditaṃ hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.62:9.14"
msgid "Evampi kho, ānanda, tathāgatassa āyatiṃ dhammasamuppādo cetasā ceto paricca vidito hotī”ti. (3) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.407, sc10
msgctxt "an6.62:10.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "an6.62:10.2"
msgid "“sakkā nu kho, bhante, imesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ puggalānaṃ aparepi tayo puggalā sappaṭibhāgā paññāpetun”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, can you describe three other persons who are counterparts of these three?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:10.3"
msgid "“Sakkā, ānandā”ti bhagavā avoca: "
msgstr "“I can, Ānanda,” said the Buddha. "

msgctxt "an6.62:10.4"
msgid "“idhāhaṃ, ānanda, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
msgstr "“Ānanda, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand: "

msgctxt "an6.62:10.5"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa vijjamānā kusalāpi dhammā akusalāpi dhammā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Both skillful and unskillful qualities are found in this person.’ "

msgctxt "an6.62:10.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aparena samayena evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
msgstr "After some time I comprehend their mind and understand: "

msgctxt "an6.62:10.7"
msgid "‘imassa kho puggalassa kusalā dhammā antarahitā, akusalā dhammā sammukhībhūtā. "
msgstr "‘The skillful qualities of this person have vanished, but the unskillful qualities are still present. "

msgctxt "an6.62:10.8"
msgid "Atthi ca khvassa kusalamūlaṃ asamucchinnaṃ, tampi sabbena sabbaṃ samugghātaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "Nevertheless, their skillful root is unbroken, but it’s about to be totally destroyed. "

msgctxt "an6.62:10.9"
msgid "Evamayaṃ puggalo āyatiṃ parihānadhammo bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "So this person is still liable to decline in the future.’ "

msgctxt "an6.62:10.10"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, aṅgārāni ādittāni sampajjalitāni sajotibhūtāni puthusilāya nikkhittāni. "
msgstr "Suppose that there were some burning coals, blazing and glowing. And they were placed on a broad rock. "

msgctxt "an6.62:10.11"
msgid "Jāneyyāsi tvaṃ, ānanda, nayimāni aṅgārāni vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissantī”ti? "
msgstr "Wouldn’t you know that those coals would not grow, increase, and spread?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:10.12"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: sāyanhasamayaṃ → sāyaṇhasamaye (s1-3) | sāyaṇhasamayaṃ (pts1) | sāyanhasamaye (mr)
msgctxt "an6.62:10.13"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi vā pana, ānanda, sāyanhasamayaṃ sūriye ogacchante, jāneyyāsi tvaṃ, ānanda, āloko antaradhāyissati andhakāro pātubhavissatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Or suppose it was the late afternoon and the sun was going down. Wouldn’t you know that the light was about to vanish and darkness appear?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:10.14"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

# NOTE: See BB’s note. He follows reading abhidose, however this reading is repeated in the next case, where it is impossible. I follow texts’ abhido, and take it as an idiom meaning “not-divided from”, i.e. “right by”, “virtually”, “nearly”. This meaning not found in the dictionaries.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:10.15"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi vā, panānanda, abhido addharattaṃ bhattakālasamaye, jāneyyāsi tvaṃ, ānanda, āloko antarahito andhakāro pātubhūto”ti? "
msgstr "“Or suppose that it’s nearly time for the midnight meal. Wouldn’t you know that the light had vanished and the darkness appeared?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:10.16"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.62:10.17"
msgid "“Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, ānanda, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
msgstr "“In the same way, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand … "

